<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Dashboard | Student</title>
    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="./../static/favicon2.png" type="image/x-icon">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"
        integrity="sha384-1BmE4kWBq78iYhFldvKuhfTAU6auU8tT94WrHftjDbrCEXSU1oBoqyl2QvZ6jIW3" crossorigin="anonymous">
    
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./home.css">

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./studentDashboard.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.5.0/css/all.css"
        integrity="sha384-B4dIYHKNBt8Bc12p+WXckhzcICo0wtJAoU8YZTY5qE0Id1GSseTk6S+L3BlXeVIU" crossorigin="anonymous">

</head>

<body>

    <!-- navBar ====================================== -->
    <%- include('../../partials/navBar') %>

        <div class="dashboard-container">

            <!-- Student Dashboard Bullets ======================== -->
            <%- include('sBullets') %>

                <!-- Student Dashboard Body ==========================-->
                <div class="dashboard-body">

                    <p class="contact-heading">Help Centre</span> </p>

                    <div class="support-box">
                        <div class="support-content">
                            <div class="harassed">
                                <p class="harassed-text">Does Someone harass you ?</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="cyberbullied">
                                <p class="cyberbulled-text">Are you being CyberBullied ?</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="antiragging-container">
                        <div class="antiragging-content">
                            <p> &emsp; I don't want you to feel that you are alone and helpless. We are
                                all with you. â€“ Please do not
                                hesitate to ask for help.</p>

                            <p> &emsp; Any body can register a complaint of Ragging. It does not have to
                                be only the victim. If you notice an incidence of Ragging you
                                must inform. It is your duty to do so. </p>
                            <p>&emsp; You can also register a complaint of Ragging - Anonymously. You
                                must however avoid this option because without knowing details it
                                becomes difficult to take any action. We can assure you of
                                confidentiality. </p>

                            <p> &emsp; Also, the Ragging Prevention Program are ready to help. You can
                                call any time on <a href="tel:1800 180 5522"> 1800 180 5522 </a>. It is a free phone.
                                You
                                can
                                also send them E mail on <a href="mailto:helpline@antiragging.in">
                                    helpline@antiragging.in</a>.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="contact-support-box">
                        <div class="help-heading">How can we help you ?</div>
                        <div class="contact-container">
                            <div class="contact-box">
                                <div class="leftPart">
                                    <img src="./static/contact.png" alt="">
                                </div>
                                <div class="rightPart">
                                    <form action="" id="form">
                                        <label for="Name">
                                            <span class="contact-ques"> Name </span>
                                            <input type="text" placeholder="Enter Your Name" id="name">
                                        </label>
                                        <label for="email">
                                            <span class="contact-ques"> Email </span>
                                            <input type="email" placeholder="Enter Your Email" id="email">
                                        </label>
                                        <label for="subject">
                                            <span class="contact-ques"> Subject </span>
                                            <input type="text" placeholder="Write a Subject" id="subject">
                                        </label>
                                        <label for="message" class="message-ques">
                                            <span class="contact-ques"> Message </span>
                                            <textarea name="" id="" cols="26" rows="4" placeholder="Describe your Issue"
                                                id="message"></textarea>
                                        </label>
                                        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
                                    </form>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>



        </div>

        <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"
            integrity="sha384-ka7Sk0Gln4gmtz2MlQnikT1wXgYsOg+OMhuP+IlRH9sENBO0LRn5q+8nbTov4+1p"
            crossorigin="anonymous"></script>

        <script>

            document.getElementById('form').addEventListener("submit", function (e) {

                e.preventDefault();

                const name = e.srcElement[0].value;
                const email = e.srcElement[1].value;
                const subject = e.srcElement[2].value;
                const message = e.srcElement[3].value;

                const data = { name, email, subject, message }

                const Params = {
                    headers: {
                        "content-type": "application/json; charset=UTF-8"
                    },
                    body: JSON.stringify(data),
                    method: "POST"
                }

                fetch('/helpmail', Params)
                    .then(data => { return data.json() })
                    .then(res => { })
                    .catch(err => { console.log(err) })
                    document.getElementById('form').reset();
            })

        </script>



</body>

</html>